'''Lorenzo Guerrero Gutiérrez''' (13 November 1900 in [[Granada, Nicaragua|Granada]] – 15 April 1981) was a [[Nicaraguan]] politician and a close associate of Somoza family. Guerrero served as one of the [[Vice President of Nicaragua|Vice Presidents]] in the administration of [[René Schick]] from May 1963 to August 1966 and became [[President of Nicaragua]] on 4 August 1966 following the death of Schick.<ref>[http://www.vicepresidencia.gob.ni/noticias/2008/jul/vp.html History of Vicepresidency] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081025000247/http://www.vicepresidencia.gob.ni/noticias/2008/jul/vp.html |date=2008-10-25 }}</ref> Guerrero served the remainder of Schick's term and handed over the presidency to [[Anastasio Somoza Debayle]] on 1 May 1967, who in turn appointed Guerrero as his Foreign Minister. He was a relative of his predecessor [[René Schick]].

