{{Orphan|date=April 2014}}

'''Moses ha-Levi Alkabetz''' was a prominent rabbi of the first half of the sixteenth century. In around 1530 he officiated as ''[[Dayan (rabbinic judge)|dayan]]'' at [[Safed]]. He seems also to have studied the [[Kabbalah]], since [[Isaac ibn Shoshan]] of Safed wrote a kabbalistic work for him. His son was [[Solomon Alkabetz]] of Safed.

