{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}} {{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}} {{Infobox Indian politician | name = Sansuma Khunggur Bwiswmuthiary | image = | caption = | birth_date ={{Birth date and age|1960|1|1|df=y}} | birth_place =[[Kokrajhar]], [[Assam]] | residence =[[Kokrajhar]] | death_date = | death_place = | office = [[Member of Parliament|MP]] | constituency = [[Kokrajhar (Lok Sabha constituency)|Kokrajhar]] | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party =[[Bodoland People's Front]] | religion = [[Bathouism]] | spouse = Uttara Bwiswmuthiary | children = 4 sons | website = | footnotes = | date = 25 September | year = 2006 | source = https://web.archive.org/web/20060619230131/http://164.100.24.208/ls/lsmember/biodata.asp?mpsno=66 }}
'''Sansuma Khunggur Bwiswmuthiary''' ({{lang-brx| सानसुमा कुंगुर बैसोमुथियारी}} born 1 January 1960) is a member of the [[14th Lok Sabha]] of [[India]]. He represents the [[Kokrajhar (Lok Sabha constituency)|Kokrajhar]] constituency of [[Assam]].<ref name="MP">{{Cite web| last =| first =| authorlink =| vauthors =| title =Fifteenth Lok Sabha Member's Bio-profile: Bwiswmuthiary, Shri Sansuma Khunggur| work =| publisher =Government of India (NIC)| year =2012| url =http://164.100.47.132/LssNew/Members/Biography.aspx?mpsno=66| format =| doi =| accessdate =11 May 2012| deadurl =yes| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20120414232042/http://164.100.47.132/LssNew/Members/Biography.aspx?mpsno=66| archivedate =14 April 2012| df =dmy-all}}</ref> He is an [[Independent (politician)|Independent]].
Bwiswmuthiary has been elected to the [[Lok Sabha]] as an independent candidate from the [[Kokrajhar]] constituency in [[Assam]] in the years 1998, 1999 and 2004. Bwiswmuthiary is a [[Bodo people|Bodo]] nationalist, and favors the creation of an autonomous [[Bodoland]] region. His backers include the [[All Bodo Students Union]] and the [[National Democratic Alliance (India)|National Democratic Alliance]].
Bwiswmuthiary is a supporter of the [[Hyde Act|Indo-US nuclear deal]].<ref>[http://www.newindpress.com/NewsItems.asp?ID=IEH20080711093241&Page=H&Title=Top+Stories&Topic=472&] {{Dead link|date=May 2012}}</ref>
